# Warren — environment configuration.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (`cp .env.example .env`) before `docker compose up`.
# Variables are warren-namespaced (`WARREN_*`) except for cross-tool ones
# warren consumes verbatim (CANOPY_REPO_URL — optional, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
# GITHUB_TOKEN).

# ---------- required ----------

# Bearer token protecting every warren route except /healthz. Generate with
#   openssl rand -hex 32
WARREN_API_TOKEN=

# Bearer token protecting `burrow serve`'s API. The supervisor spawns
# `burrow serve --socket <path>` and burrow refuses to bind without a token,
# so this is required at warren boot. WARREN_BURROW_TOKEN below must hold
# the same value — they are the two ends of one channel. Generate with
#   openssl rand -hex 32
BURROW_API_TOKEN=

# Bearer token warren's burrow client sends to authenticate against burrow.
# Must equal BURROW_API_TOKEN above.
WARREN_BURROW_TOKEN=

# At least one provider/SCM token reaches the agent so it can call its model
# API and operate on the project repo. Both are optional at warren boot —
# only required when an agent that uses them is run.
#
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is forwarded into the sandbox by burrow's built-in
# claude-code runtime, which default-allows ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN, ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL, and CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN
# without any per-project burrow.toml [env] entry (burrow ≥ 0.2.6).
# Project-level env_passthrough through canopy burrow_config is not wired
# in V1; if you need a non-built-in runtime to receive project-specific
# env, see warren-766b (filed follow-up).
#
# Multi-provider agents (e.g. the pi runtime) read additional provider keys
# from the container env. Set whichever providers your agents use; burrow's
# piRuntime.envPassthrough forwards them into the sandbox. The supervisor
# inherits container env into both child processes by default, so just
# adding a variable here is enough — no docker-compose change required.
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN doubles as the credential the warren supervisor wires into git
# at boot (`git config --global url.https://x-access-token:$GITHUB_TOKEN@github.com/.insteadOf https://github.com/`)
# so the reap step's `git push`, project clones, and refreshes can reach
# private github.com repos without a credential helper.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# Optional provider keys for multi-provider runtimes (warren-f8c0). Burrow's
# piRuntime forwards these into the sandbox when set; unset keys are
# silently skipped.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_API_KEY=
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=
# PI_API_KEY=
# GROQ_API_KEY=
# MISTRAL_API_KEY=
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=

# ---------- optional: server bind ----------

# WARREN_BIND_HOST=0.0.0.0
# WARREN_BIND_PORT=8080
# WARREN_BIND_SOCKET=/run/warren/warren.sock      # presence flips bind to unix
# WARREN_DISABLE_UI=                                # "1" to skip serving src/ui/dist
# WARREN_UI_DIST_DIR=/app/src/ui/dist               # override UI dist path

# ---------- optional: canopy agent library ----------

# Warren ships built-in agent definitions (claude-code, sapling) that cover
# the common case — set CANOPY_REPO_URL only if you maintain a custom
# canopy library and want it loaded on top. Library agents override
# built-ins by name; new names extend the catalog.
#
# When set, warren clones the URL on first refresh (POST /agents/refresh
# or `warren register-agent <name>`) and re-discovers prompts tagged
# `agent` on every refresh.
# CANOPY_REPO_URL=https://github.com/<you>/agents.git

# ---------- optional: storage ----------

# Data root. The compose volume mounts here; warren.db, the canopy clone,
# and cloned project repos all live under it.
# WARREN_DATA_DIR=/data

# Database URL (R-13 bring-your-own-database). When unset, warren falls
# back to WARREN_DB_PATH; when both are unset, it defaults to a sqlite db
# under WARREN_DATA_DIR. WARREN_DB_URL wins when both are set.
#   sqlite:///data/warren.db   sqlite at /data/warren.db (default shape)
#   :memory:                   ephemeral in-memory sqlite (tests only)
#   postgres://user:pw@host/db postgres-backed control plane (org-scale)
# WARREN_DB_URL=sqlite:///data/warren.db
# WARREN_DB_POOL_MAX=10         pg pool size; sqlite ignores this.

# Legacy sqlite path. Synthesized into a `sqlite://` WARREN_DB_URL when
# WARREN_DB_URL is unset. Prefer WARREN_DB_URL going forward.
# WARREN_DB_PATH=/data/warren.db
# WARREN_CANOPY_DIR=/data/canopy-repo
# WARREN_PROJECTS_DIR=/data/projects

# Test substrate (R-13 step 6). Drives `withDb()` in src/db/testing.ts.
# Defaults to sqlite (today's `:memory:` path). Set both to opt into pg
# unit tests; CI exposes them in the postgres matrix job. Each `withDb()`
# call creates a fresh `warren_test_<8hex>` schema and drops it on close.
# WARREN_TEST_DIALECT=postgres
# WARREN_TEST_PG_URL=postgres://warren:warren@127.0.0.1:5432/warren_test

# Host path bind-mounted into the container at /canopy-source so a local
# (file://) canopy repo can be the source for CANOPY_REPO_URL without
# pushing to GitHub. Pair with `CANOPY_REPO_URL=file:///canopy-source`.
# Required if your CANOPY_REPO_URL uses file:///canopy-source; ignored
# otherwise. The compose mount is read-only.
# CANOPY_SOURCE_DIR=/absolute/path/to/your/canopy-repo

# ---------- optional: burrow client ----------

# Where the supervisor binds burrow's unix socket. Warren reads the same
# path to reach burrow. Default matches the in-container layout.
# WARREN_BURROW_SOCKET=/var/run/burrow.sock
# WARREN_BURROW_HOST=                               # set HOST + PORT to use TCP
# WARREN_BURROW_PORT=

# ---------- optional: supervisor ----------

# Override the binaries the supervisor execs. Defaults match the image
# layout (burrow / bun on PATH, server entry at src/server/main.ts).
# WARREN_BURROW_BIN=burrow
# WARREN_SUPERVISOR_BUN=bun
# WARREN_SERVER_ENTRY=src/server/main.ts

# Splice extra flags into `burrow serve`. NO_AUTH=1 lets warren boot on a
# loopback-only dev box without BURROW_API_TOKEN; ARGS is an escape hatch
# for flags warren doesn't model explicitly (whitespace-separated).
# WARREN_BURROW_NO_AUTH=1
# WARREN_BURROW_ARGS=--log-level debug

# ---------- optional: tooling ----------

# WARREN_GIT_BINARY=git
# WARREN_CN_BINARY=cn
# WARREN_LOG_LEVEL=info

# ---------- optional: agent git identity (warren-fe67) ----------

# Per-deployment git identity for agent commits. When both are set, the
# supervisor runs `git config --global user.name/user.email` (so burrow's
# default `user` identity mode mirrors them into the workspace) and exports
# GIT_AUTHOR_NAME / GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL / GIT_COMMITTER_NAME / GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL
# into child processes. Unset → falls back to host git identity (typically
# unconfigured in a fresh container).
#
# Use a github.com noreply email so commits attribute to the operator's
# GitHub account and the contribution graph reflects agent-driven work.
# Find your numeric id at https://api.github.com/users/<your-login>; the
# noreply format is `<id>+<login>@users.noreply.github.com`.
# WARREN_GIT_AUTHOR_NAME=Warren
# WARREN_GIT_AUTHOR_EMAIL=1234567+yourlogin@users.noreply.github.com

# ---------- optional: pull-request auto-open (warren-f6af) ----------

# After reap pushes the agent's branch, warren can open a GitHub PR for
# it automatically. Default ON. Set to "false" / "0" / "no" / "off" to
# disable globally. Skips silently when the run isn't successful, the
# push lands no commits, the branch matches the project default, or
# GITHUB_TOKEN is unset.
# WARREN_AUTO_OPEN_PR=true

# Optional warren UI base URL embedded in the PR body so reviewers can
# jump back to the run that produced the change. Omit to skip the link.
# WARREN_BASE_URL=https://warren.example.com

# ---------- optional: run-branch prefix (warren-9993) ----------

# Warren composes the burrow workspace branch as `<prefix>/<run.id>`. The
# legacy default `burrow` ships unchanged; agents looking at `git log` /
# PR review often mistake `burrow/<id>` branches as living in the burrow
# repo. Set this per-deployment to a friendlier prefix (e.g. `warren`,
# `agent`, `bot`) and the branch becomes `warren/run_xxxxxxxxxxxx`.
#
# Per-project `.warren/defaults.json.runBranchPrefix` wins over this env
# value when both are set. Validation: kebab/snake-case (lowercase,
# digits, dots, dashes, underscores); invalid values silently fall back to
# the next precedence slot — they never block a spawn.
# WARREN_RUN_BRANCH_PREFIX=warren
